L2-Development 
 
Correct me if I'm wrong but I dug into RDS Proxy a bit more and there's a wrinkle. That token from generate-db-auth-token is IAM-based and only lasts 15 min, and it turns out RDS Proxy → Aurora doesn't support IAM auth due to AWS limitation it only takes a static password from Secrets Manager. Good news is the Lambda still uses IAM through the proxy, so IAM auth stays end-user-side. For the proxy's own login, we'd just need a static password stored in Secrets Manager. Two ways to do it: New non-person role with a password, same priv_* as pgsi_ans00315015 or Add a password to pgsi_ans00315015 alongside the IAM auth
 
