I think the 15-min thing might be from the IAM auth token, that one expires every 15 min. Secrets Manager rotation is different right, you set the schedule yourself 30 days or 90 days, whatever we want right. RDS Proxy handles rotation automatically too, so when Secrets Manager rotates it, the proxy picks up the new password without any downtime. So basically what we need is a normal DB password for pgsi_ans00315015 or a new role, whichever's easier, stored in Secrets Manager on a normal rotation schedule. Same as any regular service account.
 
